1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,367
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,367 --> 00:00:02,600
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,775 --> 00:00:07,375
Anyway, it's late.

4
00:00:07,375 --> 00:00:09,131
Do you think
your mother left dinner for us?

5
00:00:09,644 --> 00:00:12,344
Don't worry.
No matter how mad my mom gets,

6
00:00:12,645 --> 00:00:13,989
she believes in feeding people
before scolding them.

7
00:00:14,406 --> 00:00:17,160
As long as we have rice,
I can whip up whatever you're craving.

8
00:00:17,799 --> 00:00:18,799
Yes, Chef.

9
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:21,277
Wait for me, Driver Cho.

10
00:00:41,359 --> 00:00:43,159
All right, it's done.

11
00:00:45,988 --> 00:00:48,163
I'm telling you,
you had to have been a chef.

12
00:00:48,635 --> 00:00:51,096
What did I tell you?
Taste it before you judge.

13
00:00:51,096 --> 00:00:52,096
Go ahead and eat.

14
00:00:52,096 --> 00:00:53,229
Thank you for the meal, Chef.

15
00:00:59,646 --> 00:01:00,765
This is really good.

16
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,579
Want some of mine too?
I haven't touched it yet.

17
00:01:04,224 --> 00:01:06,339
No thanks. Do I look like a pig to you?

18
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:11,611
Seriously, when did you learn to cook?

19
00:01:12,181 --> 00:01:13,781
You're practically a professional.

20
00:01:13,781 --> 00:01:16,355
I've lived on my own for over ten years.

21
00:01:16,621 --> 00:01:18,283
I had no choice
if I didn't want to starve.

22
00:01:18,488 --> 00:01:19,888
I had to cook for myself.

23
00:01:20,488 --> 00:01:24,288
Sometimes, I can't believe
you're a third-generation heir.

24
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:27,405
What kind of wealthy heir
cooks his own meals?

25
00:01:27,648 --> 00:01:29,400
Even if you studied abroad alone,
it doesn't make sense.

26
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,035
Silly you.

27
00:01:33,181 --> 00:01:36,928
Am I really eating omurice made
by a wealthy heir? Amazing.

28
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,800
You'll wake your parents. Quiet.

29
00:01:40,591 --> 00:01:41,591
Eat quietly.

30
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:46,667
Honey.

31
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,741
Something's off with Bit Na.

32
00:01:51,596 --> 00:01:52,629
What do you mean?

33
00:01:52,629 --> 00:01:55,367
She's had no energy all day
and barely ate.

34
00:01:55,867 --> 00:01:59,528
She even skipped her snack
and slept all afternoon.

35
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,475
You don't think she's sick, do you?

36
00:02:03,244 --> 00:02:04,453
I don't think that's it.

37
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,167
Could it be because she misses her mom?

38
00:02:08,293 --> 00:02:10,344
Should I call
and ask when she's coming back?

39
00:02:10,344 --> 00:02:12,944
Eun Hyeong already said
it'd take about a week.

40
00:02:14,836 --> 00:02:16,200
I just have a bad feeling.

41
00:02:17,293 --> 00:02:19,475
What if something happened to them again?

42
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,667
Thank you for the meal.

43
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:23,675
Quiet. We need to clean up quietly.

44
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,323
I thought Eun Ae and Team Manager Ko...

45
00:02:25,915 --> 00:02:28,032
would eat outside before coming home.
I guess not.

46
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:32,533
No, you stay here. I'll go out.

47
00:02:32,664 --> 00:02:33,728
I have something to say to Eun Ae anyway.

48
00:02:34,368 --> 00:02:35,461
- All right, then.
- Okay.

49
00:02:45,219 --> 00:02:46,765
It's fine. Leave it.

50
00:02:46,899 --> 00:02:49,323
You made such a delicious omurice,
so I'll do the dishes.

51
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:51,208
If you've got time for that,

52
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:53,608
go upstairs and work on the Joy upgrade.

53
00:02:53,608 --> 00:02:54,997
And stop interfering with my hobby.

54
00:02:55,195 --> 00:02:57,349
Hey now, this is my specialty.

55
00:02:57,349 --> 00:02:58,349
Give me those gloves.

56
00:02:59,505 --> 00:03:02,388
Then, just sit here and...

57
00:03:02,388 --> 00:03:04,968
admire how artistically I do the dishes.

58
00:03:06,512 --> 00:03:08,915
At this level,
your self-love is incurable.

59
00:03:09,768 --> 00:03:10,768
Then let's do it together.

60
00:03:16,788 --> 00:03:18,376
Dad, you're still awake?

61
00:03:18,845 --> 00:03:20,029
Did we wake you up?

62
00:03:20,899 --> 00:03:22,720
Why is Team Manager Ko doing the dishes?

63
00:03:23,792 --> 00:03:26,515
He said it was his hobby, so I let him.

64
00:03:27,002 --> 00:03:28,603
There aren't many.
I'll be done in no time.

65
00:03:29,967 --> 00:03:31,300
Can I talk to you for a minute?

66
00:03:31,683 --> 00:03:33,347
What? Sure.

67
00:03:34,179 --> 00:03:35,693
Finish up quickly and go get some rest.

68
00:03:35,693 --> 00:03:36,693
Okay.

69
00:03:41,427 --> 00:03:43,512
What do you mean?

70
00:03:43,691 --> 00:03:45,651
You're asking what kind of relationship
I have with Team Manager Ko?

71
00:03:46,343 --> 00:03:48,037
Dads have instincts too.

72
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,891
The two of you are always together,
even when commuting.

73
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,915
And then there was that night...

74
00:03:52,915 --> 00:03:55,181
you spent together in the yard,
among other things.

75
00:03:55,432 --> 00:03:58,355
That's because we live in the same house
and work on the same team.

76
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,589
And that night,
someone locked the front door,

77
00:04:02,256 --> 00:04:04,787
so I called Eun Nim to let us in,
but she didn't answer.

78
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:06,541
I sent her a text
and kept talking with the Team Manager,

79
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,643
then accidentally fell asleep.

80
00:04:08,989 --> 00:04:10,967
That's really all there is to it?

81
00:04:11,213 --> 00:04:14,392
What? What else would there be?

82
00:04:15,071 --> 00:04:17,856
I want to know what's in your heart.

83
00:04:20,022 --> 00:04:21,022
Dad.

84
00:04:23,276 --> 00:04:26,907
The truth is, I like Team Manager Ko.

85
00:04:28,627 --> 00:04:29,627
Really?

86
00:04:30,147 --> 00:04:31,767
At first, I wasn't sure.

87
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:34,576
But as time passed, I realized how I feel.

88
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:37,100
Then how does Team Manager Ko feel?

89
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,925
I don't know. I haven't asked him.

90
00:04:40,798 --> 00:04:43,613
But regardless of how he feels,

91
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:45,219
I'm sure of my own feelings.

92
00:04:46,855 --> 00:04:49,784
Do you not like that I like him?

93
00:04:50,794 --> 00:04:52,927
I'm genuinely happy and excited...

94
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,960
that you've found someone you like.

95
00:04:55,328 --> 00:04:58,336
But I don't want to see you get hurt.

96
00:04:59,659 --> 00:05:01,560
Why do you think I'll get hurt?

97
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:05,101
Is it because you think it'll end up
like what happened with Ji Hun before?

98
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,544
I know Team Manager Ko
isn't that kind of person, but...

99
00:05:09,181 --> 00:05:13,126
As far as I know,
once this competition is over...

100
00:05:13,126 --> 00:05:15,739
He's going back to the U.S.

101
00:05:17,371 --> 00:05:21,307
Right. I don't know
how serious things are between you two,

102
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,427
but I'm worried
you might get hurt later on.

103
00:05:25,232 --> 00:05:26,667
That's what concerns me.

104
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,683
It's not like
I haven't thought about that.

105
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:32,016
But it hasn't happened yet.

106
00:05:32,518 --> 00:05:35,218
Right now,
I'm just focusing on how I feel.

107
00:05:36,036 --> 00:05:38,419
Of course, he may not feel the same way.

108
00:05:39,732 --> 00:05:41,328
Anyway, be careful.

109
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:45,267
Make sure neither of you gets hurt, okay?

110
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,000
Yes, Dad.

111
00:05:56,414 --> 00:05:59,960
Like I can control when I cough.

112
00:06:00,062 --> 00:06:01,456
Go on before someone sees us.

113
00:06:05,181 --> 00:06:07,979
As long as we have rice,
I can whip up whatever you're craving.

114
00:06:08,818 --> 00:06:09,818
Yes, Chef.

115
00:06:10,951 --> 00:06:12,218
Wait for me, Driver Cho.

116
00:06:26,923 --> 00:06:28,997
Seo Seung Ri, what are you doing here?

117
00:06:33,511 --> 00:06:34,511
You're late.

118
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:39,867
I'm exhausted.

119
00:06:40,867 --> 00:06:43,955
I've been drained all day.
I can barely stand.

120
00:06:44,192 --> 00:06:45,800
Why? Did something happen?

121
00:06:46,549 --> 00:06:50,029
There's someone
I just want to smash to pieces,

122
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,104
but I can't.

123
00:06:54,548 --> 00:06:56,659
Is that writer giving you
that much trouble?

124
00:07:01,667 --> 00:07:04,059
She couldn't be worse than Gyeol.

125
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:06,567
What?

126
00:07:07,767 --> 00:07:11,368
When the world's greatest Seo Seung Ri...

127
00:07:12,783 --> 00:07:15,597
is sitting here
looking like she's lost everything,

128
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:17,267
it's pretty obvious what's going on.

129
00:07:18,946 --> 00:07:20,981
I can't believe I'm actually having
a conversation with you.

130
00:07:21,523 --> 00:07:23,144
Get up. Mom and Dad are waiting.

131
00:07:23,819 --> 00:07:24,819
You know,

132
00:07:27,267 --> 00:07:29,667
ever since we were kids,
I've always thought you were amazing.

133
00:07:31,811 --> 00:07:33,629
It wasn't exactly admiration, but...

134
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:35,310
I was still proud...

135
00:07:36,647 --> 00:07:38,560
that you were my sister.

136
00:07:40,154 --> 00:07:41,611
You're pretty and kind.

137
00:07:42,975 --> 00:07:45,237
You're smart, and you can sing.

138
00:07:45,992 --> 00:07:48,451
You've got a mean punch,
and you can dance.

139
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,699
Actually, maybe not the dancing part.

140
00:07:52,943 --> 00:07:54,476
What else was there?

141
00:07:55,843 --> 00:07:56,843
Anyway,

142
00:07:58,943 --> 00:08:01,691
you're perfect at everything.

143
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,875
So with that smart brain of yours,

144
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,399
why are you hanging on to something
that won't work?

145
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:14,987
If it's not meant to happen,
it's not meant to happen.

146
00:08:21,013 --> 00:08:24,237
Seriously, you're driving me crazy.

147
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:25,867
You're going to keep running your mouth?

148
00:08:27,659 --> 00:08:29,867
Idiot. Blockhead.

149
00:08:32,238 --> 00:08:33,238
That punk.

150
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:38,792
You're right.

151
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:41,341
I really am an idiot and a blockhead.

152
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:49,300
(Chief Ko Min Ho)

153
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:04,008
Did she get home all right?
I should've given her a ride.

154
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,117
This business trip is D-Day.

155
00:09:17,588 --> 00:09:19,488
Let's do this, Ko Min Ho.

156
00:09:29,659 --> 00:09:32,675
Seung Ri said she was coming home earlier.
Why isn't she here yet?

157
00:09:37,871 --> 00:09:38,871
You're not asleep?

158
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,467
No. I wanted to show Seung Ri
and Seung Wu before going to bed.

159
00:09:42,705 --> 00:09:45,421
What? Are you a kid?

160
00:09:47,627 --> 00:09:49,557
- I'm home.
- How are you here already?

161
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:51,595
Come here. Sit down, both of you.

162
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:01,269
Ta-da. Dad got me a gift.

163
00:10:01,816 --> 00:10:02,883
It's a diamond.

164
00:10:02,883 --> 00:10:04,533
What? A diamond?

165
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:08,440
You really went all out, Dad.

166
00:10:08,579 --> 00:10:10,789
It's not a natural diamond.
It's a lab-grown diamond.

167
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:13,749
I didn't even know those existed
until today.

168
00:10:13,851 --> 00:10:15,784
A lab-grown diamond? What's that?

169
00:10:15,784 --> 00:10:17,051
A diamond discovered by a rapper?

170
00:10:17,853 --> 00:10:20,741
<i>Yo, a diamond discovered by a rapper!
Yeah</i>

171
00:10:23,876 --> 00:10:25,736
It's not formed in nature.

172
00:10:26,131 --> 00:10:28,592
It's made in a lab
with the exact same composition.

173
00:10:29,438 --> 00:10:32,438
Natural diamonds are way beyond my budget.

174
00:10:33,276 --> 00:10:36,704
So it's the same thing,
just from a different birthplace.

175
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:39,315
So what? It's still a diamond.

176
00:10:39,315 --> 00:10:42,213
Our youngest
actually said something smart for once.

177
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,189
All right, put it on me.

178
00:10:44,898 --> 00:10:48,198
You can do it yourself.

179
00:10:48,546 --> 00:10:49,546
Hurry up.

180
00:10:49,645 --> 00:10:51,212
You should put it on her yourself, Dad.

181
00:10:51,527 --> 00:10:54,472
Exactly. If you're going to move her,
go all the way.

182
00:11:06,183 --> 00:11:08,283
What do you think? Do you like the design?

183
00:11:10,846 --> 00:11:12,581
It's beautiful. It looks great on you.

184
00:11:13,707 --> 00:11:15,283
I'll head in now.

185
00:11:19,023 --> 00:11:20,160
What's with her now?

186
00:11:24,274 --> 00:11:26,733
Wait, Mr. Cho's wife came to our house?

187
00:11:27,171 --> 00:11:30,579
Yeah.
She brought a whole pot of oxtail soup...

188
00:11:30,664 --> 00:11:33,608
and chatted with Mother
for nearly an hour.

189
00:11:34,536 --> 00:11:36,096
What could she possibly be up to?

190
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,957
It's probably nothing.

191
00:11:38,568 --> 00:11:41,549
Last time, she seemed really bothered...

192
00:11:41,549 --> 00:11:42,912
that Mother cooked and left
without eating.

193
00:11:43,239 --> 00:11:44,491
That's probably all it was.

194
00:11:44,892 --> 00:11:48,285
Besides,
Seong Jun's always been a straight arrow.

195
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:50,315
They say married couples grow alike too.

196
00:11:51,391 --> 00:11:54,704
Your friend may be decent,
but not that woman.

197
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:58,050
You think everyone is as sincere
as you are?

198
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:00,150
Not a chance.

199
00:12:00,416 --> 00:12:01,784
You're too kind for your own good.

200
00:12:02,891 --> 00:12:04,501
Well, I can't deny
I do have that side of me.

201
00:12:05,988 --> 00:12:09,037
In that case,
how about we raise a toast tonight?

202
00:12:09,296 --> 00:12:11,419
A toast? For what?

203
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,605
Because the split is off the table?

204
00:12:16,071 --> 00:12:17,651
Come on. "Off the table?"

205
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:20,005
Watch your language, Crystal.

206
00:12:20,187 --> 00:12:23,349
Whatever you call it,
it's great news for us.

207
00:12:23,904 --> 00:12:26,048
But,
instead of just the two of us celebrating,

208
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:27,467
how about inviting Min Ho too?

209
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:29,567
That's a great idea.

210
00:12:29,967 --> 00:12:31,544
Yeah. Min Ho's been working himself
to the bone...

211
00:12:31,544 --> 00:12:34,427
preparing for that second round.
We should cheer him on.

212
00:12:34,686 --> 00:12:36,344
- Right.
- Let's go.

213
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:38,077
- Off the table.
- Not off the table.

214
00:12:38,077 --> 00:12:39,602
Let's head outside.

215
00:12:39,602 --> 00:12:41,699
- Right. Outside it is.
- Outside.

216
00:12:42,067 --> 00:12:43,315
What's with the sudden celebration?

217
00:12:44,243 --> 00:12:47,243
The second round of the competition
is practically in the bag.

218
00:12:47,243 --> 00:12:48,652
We're just celebrating early.

219
00:12:48,652 --> 00:12:49,813
Come on, raise your glass.

220
00:12:50,063 --> 00:12:51,645
Dad, you said it yourself before.

221
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:53,315
You said that Gyeol wasn't someone
to underestimate.

222
00:12:54,102 --> 00:12:55,443
Then why have you changed your mind now?

223
00:12:55,616 --> 00:12:56,616
This punk...

224
00:12:57,115 --> 00:13:00,645
Back then, I underestimated you too much,
and I'm sorry for that.

225
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:02,589
But now I see it.

226
00:13:02,835 --> 00:13:05,075
Gyeol's just going to pursue
his own ideals...

227
00:13:05,403 --> 00:13:08,075
while Grandpa's around
and then head back to the U.S.

228
00:13:08,313 --> 00:13:09,965
So you can relax now.

229
00:13:10,367 --> 00:13:13,603
Min Ho, my arm's going to fall off.
Come on, let's toast.

230
00:13:14,328 --> 00:13:16,367
Raise your glass. That's it. Cheers.

231
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:17,995
À votre santé.

232
00:13:23,299 --> 00:13:25,835
Right. Speaking of Gyeol,

233
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:29,467
it looks like things are really heating up
between him and Mr. Cho's daughter.

234
00:13:30,789 --> 00:13:33,795
Is that why he moved out?
So he could date more freely?

235
00:13:34,256 --> 00:13:37,571
Really? Then what about Seung Ri?

236
00:13:37,976 --> 00:13:40,592
Seung Ri's now the foal left chasing
after a chicken she can't catch.

237
00:13:41,192 --> 00:13:42,192
Dog.

238
00:13:42,928 --> 00:13:46,200
It's "The dog that chased the chicken
ends up staring at the roof."

239
00:13:47,059 --> 00:13:49,971
Whether it's a foal or a dog,
neither can get on the roof anyway.

240
00:13:49,973 --> 00:13:50,973
That's true.

241
00:13:50,973 --> 00:13:52,443
Mom, Dad, watch what you say.

242
00:13:52,443 --> 00:13:55,568
You startled me. Why are you shouting?

243
00:13:58,667 --> 00:13:59,667
Dad,

244
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:04,368
you three were supposedly best friends
in high school.

245
00:14:04,491 --> 00:14:05,811
How did you lose touch?

246
00:14:06,813 --> 00:14:07,813
What?

247
00:14:08,019 --> 00:14:10,947
Come to think of it,
you've never told me...

248
00:14:10,947 --> 00:14:12,792
that the three of you were best friends.

249
00:14:13,493 --> 00:14:16,880
More importantly, how did Mr. Seo
end up joining our company?

250
00:14:17,184 --> 00:14:19,869
And if you were best friends
back in high school,

251
00:14:19,869 --> 00:14:21,429
why do you act like
you can't stand each other now...

252
00:14:21,429 --> 00:14:22,645
Enough!

253
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,816
We were having a nice celebration,

254
00:14:24,816 --> 00:14:26,451
so why bring up ancient history?

255
00:14:26,451 --> 00:14:27,949
Seriously.

256
00:14:28,436 --> 00:14:29,436
Honestly.

257
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:33,637
We're done drinking,
so this gathering is over.

258
00:14:33,936 --> 00:14:34,936
Already?

259
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:38,867
Look who's saying that
after finishing everything.

260
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:42,386
Min Ho and I have to be at work
early tomorrow.

261
00:14:42,386 --> 00:14:43,813
Come on, let's go.

262
00:14:44,529 --> 00:14:45,728
All right.

263
00:14:46,243 --> 00:14:48,056
Good night, son. Bonne nuit.

264
00:14:48,924 --> 00:14:50,893
What's gotten into him?

265
00:15:03,284 --> 00:15:05,467
Let me get some sleep already.

266
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:09,619
You used to get ready in three minutes.
Now you're at it for 30.

267
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:12,967
That's a new outfit.

268
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:16,147
How do I look?
I did a little online shopping.

269
00:15:16,608 --> 00:15:18,517
The power of love really is amazing.

270
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,667
The engineering caveman
has finally shed her skin...

271
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:23,320
and transformed into a butterfly.

272
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:24,560
What are you saying?

273
00:15:25,794 --> 00:15:28,811
But would it look weird
if I wore a dress to work when I never do?

274
00:15:29,168 --> 00:15:32,965
Whether you wear pants or a sack,
nobody cares.

275
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,984
Just get to work already.

276
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:38,343
Maybe Team Manager Ko will care.

277
00:15:38,532 --> 00:15:39,532
What?

278
00:15:39,532 --> 00:15:41,867
Then again,
he's the reason you're wearing it.

279
00:15:42,251 --> 00:15:44,251
If he doesn't notice,
you'll be disappointed, won't you?

280
00:15:44,855 --> 00:15:46,493
Stop talking nonsense!

281
00:15:48,412 --> 00:15:52,155
I'm going back to sleep.
Tell Mom I'm skipping breakfast.

282
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,720
I was working until dawn.

283
00:15:55,559 --> 00:15:56,959
All right. Sleep.

284
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:16,853
I'm coming in.

285
00:16:21,369 --> 00:16:24,499
Sorry! I didn't see anything. Really.

286
00:16:26,416 --> 00:16:27,944
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

287
00:16:35,421 --> 00:16:36,896
What's going on all of a sudden?

288
00:16:37,504 --> 00:16:40,261
I knocked several times...

289
00:16:40,261 --> 00:16:41,963
and said I was coming in.

290
00:16:42,491 --> 00:16:44,896
Sorry.
I couldn't hear you over the hair dryer.

291
00:16:45,267 --> 00:16:46,572
Did you need something urgently?

292
00:16:46,955 --> 00:16:48,091
Today...

293
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:14,067
What about today, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

294
00:17:17,267 --> 00:17:19,829
Today...

295
00:17:20,056 --> 00:17:22,500
Let's take the bus instead of my scooter.

296
00:17:23,171 --> 00:17:24,171
Why?

297
00:17:24,423 --> 00:17:28,165
My outfit today isn't really suitable
for riding a scooter.

298
00:17:37,564 --> 00:17:38,564
You look so pret...

299
00:17:39,967 --> 00:17:42,917
Do you have a blind date or something?

300
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:45,485
A blind date? Of course not.

301
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:49,100
Come on. If we're even a little late,
traffic will be awful.

302
00:17:49,499 --> 00:17:50,799
All right. I'll be right out.

303
00:17:53,967 --> 00:17:55,400
That's a photo of the Chairman.

304
00:17:57,767 --> 00:17:58,995
Who is this?

305
00:17:59,725 --> 00:18:01,565
That's...

306
00:18:01,923 --> 00:18:03,156
Aren't we late?

307
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,405
Right. I'll head downstairs first.

308
00:18:06,212 --> 00:18:07,212
Sure.

309
00:18:13,706 --> 00:18:16,645
Father, that's the girl.

310
00:18:18,099 --> 00:18:19,099
Isn't she pretty?

311
00:18:23,604 --> 00:18:25,304
(Kangsu Construction)

312
00:18:27,886 --> 00:18:29,912
- Good morning.
- Morning.

313
00:18:32,539 --> 00:18:34,896
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
are you going on a blind date today?

314
00:18:35,216 --> 00:18:38,315
What? No, of course not.

315
00:18:47,004 --> 00:18:49,704
Ms. Cho, you look so pretty today.

316
00:18:50,197 --> 00:18:52,144
Want to go on a blind date?

317
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:54,467
What? A blind date?

318
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:57,667
There's a wine club gathering tonight.
Come with me.

319
00:18:58,414 --> 00:19:01,584
Ms. Cho, is the Joy upgrade finished?

320
00:19:05,653 --> 00:19:06,953
Almost.

321
00:19:07,832 --> 00:19:10,275
The upgrade's already done?

322
00:19:10,686 --> 00:19:12,563
When does an upgrade ever end?

323
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:14,405
You improve it, then improve it again,
and again.

324
00:19:18,435 --> 00:19:19,960
I'll stop by Chief Ko's office.

325
00:19:22,542 --> 00:19:24,875
You've already picked the location
for the business trip? Where?

326
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:26,380
Anywhere.

327
00:19:27,352 --> 00:19:28,352
Anywhere?

328
00:19:28,524 --> 00:19:30,053
Anywhere but the Planning Office.

329
00:19:32,169 --> 00:19:33,907
What's wrong? Did something happen?

330
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,767
Do you already know, Chief?

331
00:19:37,059 --> 00:19:38,059
Know what?

332
00:19:38,059 --> 00:19:40,526
That Ms. Cho Eun Ae
and Team Manager Ko live together.

333
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:42,600
How did you find out?

334
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:45,261
So you did know.

335
00:19:46,494 --> 00:19:47,494
Let's go outside first.

336
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:52,435
So you're so shocked
that they're living together...

337
00:19:52,927 --> 00:19:55,235
that you want to go anywhere
they won't be?

338
00:19:56,572 --> 00:19:57,819
I can't do that.

339
00:20:00,354 --> 00:20:01,869
Deal with it. Get over it yourself.

340
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,200
And accept their relationship too.

341
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:06,160
Then we can go.

342
00:20:07,296 --> 00:20:08,661
Then I'll take the day off today.

343
00:20:09,205 --> 00:20:12,272
What? We're just getting started
on the second round of the competition.

344
00:20:12,272 --> 00:20:15,291
You're going to stop preparing
because of something like this?

345
00:20:15,463 --> 00:20:17,144
Should I just quit altogether then?

346
00:20:17,445 --> 00:20:18,528
Manager Seo!

347
00:20:21,465 --> 00:20:24,037
Understood. I'll prepare for the meeting.

348
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:26,691
You're not looking at houses today either?

349
00:20:27,463 --> 00:20:29,272
What could possibly keep you this busy?

350
00:20:29,822 --> 00:20:32,435
I'll explain everything
when I get home later.

351
00:20:34,421 --> 00:20:35,757
Bit Na's doing well, right?

352
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,608
I don't know. Maybe it's because
she hasn't seen her mother in a while,

353
00:20:38,608 --> 00:20:40,459
but she's had no energy since yesterday.

354
00:20:41,476 --> 00:20:43,571
Nothing's going on
with your family, right?

355
00:20:44,044 --> 00:20:46,349
Mother, I'm busy right now.
I'll call later.

356
00:20:46,831 --> 00:20:47,831
I'm hanging up.

357
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,367
Hey, Eun Hyeong. Cho Eun Hyeong!

358
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:54,904
Seriously.

359
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,067
(Mutual Divorce Confirmation Application)

360
00:21:04,124 --> 00:21:08,864
Is this really the only way?

361
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:14,251
Right now, it's the best option.

362
00:21:15,822 --> 00:21:19,349
Ji Seon, let's think this through
one more time.

363
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:21,213
I'm really okay with everything, you know?

364
00:21:22,146 --> 00:21:24,109
So what if we lost the deposit?

365
00:21:24,445 --> 00:21:26,605
We'll find a way to keep going.

366
00:21:28,422 --> 00:21:29,422
How?

367
00:21:30,912 --> 00:21:32,712
How exactly do you think we'll keep going?

368
00:21:33,626 --> 00:21:36,608
Kierkegaard said love isn't a feeling
but a duty.

369
00:21:36,608 --> 00:21:37,820
And right now, that duty...

370
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:40,056
Stop. Please stop.

371
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:44,867
I don't have time to listen
to your philosophy lectures anymore.

372
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:48,739
I need to save every second...

373
00:21:49,172 --> 00:21:50,851
to earn money and pay off the debt.

374
00:21:52,128 --> 00:21:53,933
And earn child support for Bit Na.

375
00:21:54,319 --> 00:21:56,411
Ji Seon, please.

376
00:21:59,432 --> 00:22:03,621
Is money really all we can talk about now?

377
00:22:05,211 --> 00:22:08,715
Is money the only thing
that matters to us?

378
00:22:10,029 --> 00:22:11,168
Then what else is there?

379
00:22:12,253 --> 00:22:13,767
What do we have left?

380
00:22:14,943 --> 00:22:16,736
The only reason
I'm not talking about Bit Na...

381
00:22:17,732 --> 00:22:19,581
is because I trust you with that.

382
00:22:20,645 --> 00:22:23,328
I know you'll raise Bit Na...

383
00:22:23,328 --> 00:22:25,267
better than anyone else could.

384
00:22:30,735 --> 00:22:31,735
Sign it.

385
00:22:41,779 --> 00:22:48,448
(Husband)

386
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:52,910
Thank you.

387
00:22:54,304 --> 00:22:55,371
And I'm sorry.

388
00:22:57,288 --> 00:22:58,388
I'll see you at court tomorrow.

389
00:23:34,724 --> 00:23:36,171
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

390
00:23:38,767 --> 00:23:39,767
Mom...

391
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:43,807
Mom's so sorry.

392
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:13,651
Mother, what's with all the kimchi?

393
00:24:15,672 --> 00:24:17,304
I'm taking some to Gyeol.

394
00:24:18,287 --> 00:24:22,149
He's living alone.
How is he supposed to eat all that?

395
00:24:22,922 --> 00:24:27,219
The family he lives with
even feeds him breakfast and dinner.

396
00:24:27,788 --> 00:24:29,008
I'm taking it to them.

397
00:24:30,619 --> 00:24:32,267
Is Gyeol boarding somewhere?

398
00:24:33,779 --> 00:24:35,760
When your child moves out,

399
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:39,181
you should at least check
where he's living...

400
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:42,096
and what he's eating.

401
00:24:42,302 --> 00:24:45,163
He's been living away from home
for over ten years.

402
00:24:45,368 --> 00:24:46,816
He moved to the U.S. ages ago.

403
00:24:48,349 --> 00:24:49,488
Father.

404
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:50,965
- Back from your walk?
- Yeah.

405
00:24:51,139 --> 00:24:54,013
You must be hungry. I'll start lunch soon.

406
00:24:54,848 --> 00:24:56,795
Since I've made kimchi,
how about chopped noodles?

407
00:24:56,957 --> 00:25:00,333
Anything you make sounds good to me,
Yeong Hwa.

408
00:25:01,871 --> 00:25:03,797
Just thinking about fresh kimchi
and chopped noodles...

409
00:25:04,688 --> 00:25:06,171
is making my mouth water.

410
00:25:06,893 --> 00:25:10,547
Right. After lunch,
I need you to drive me somewhere.

411
00:25:11,074 --> 00:25:13,200
Sure. Where are you going?

412
00:25:14,248 --> 00:25:15,475
Since I already made the kimchi,

413
00:25:16,224 --> 00:25:18,691
I want to take some
to Gyeol's boarding house.

414
00:25:18,885 --> 00:25:20,288
Should I come too?

415
00:25:21,344 --> 00:25:22,344
What for?

416
00:25:22,636 --> 00:25:23,869
I'm just dropping off some kimchi...

417
00:25:24,136 --> 00:25:26,944
and side dishes
with the family he lives with.

418
00:25:27,715 --> 00:25:30,768
The noodles will take another hour,
so go rest.

419
00:25:31,274 --> 00:25:32,274
All right then.

420
00:25:33,238 --> 00:25:35,549
Instead of just watching, help out.

421
00:25:36,786 --> 00:25:39,016
Me? Okay then...

422
00:25:39,558 --> 00:25:42,137
Mother, should I roll out the noodles?

423
00:25:42,137 --> 00:25:43,419
Where's the rolling pin?

424
00:25:43,904 --> 00:25:45,960
You've heard things here and there.

425
00:25:46,911 --> 00:25:49,232
Do you even know
what a rolling pin looks like?

426
00:25:51,916 --> 00:25:54,242
A rolling pin is a rolling pin.

427
00:25:54,242 --> 00:25:55,691
He's ridiculous.

428
00:25:57,328 --> 00:25:58,363
I'll help too.

429
00:26:02,238 --> 00:26:03,238
Yes, Grandma.

430
00:26:04,538 --> 00:26:06,638
What? My address?

431
00:26:10,867 --> 00:26:12,485
Why do you need my address
all of a sudden?

432
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,195
What do you mean, all of a sudden?

433
00:26:14,731 --> 00:26:16,333
I've been meaning to visit for a while.

434
00:26:16,576 --> 00:26:18,853
I just kept putting it off
because I wasn't feeling well.

435
00:26:20,337 --> 00:26:21,937
Since I made kimchi today,

436
00:26:21,937 --> 00:26:23,920
I'm just going to drop some off
at the house,

437
00:26:24,386 --> 00:26:25,419
so send me the address.

438
00:26:25,419 --> 00:26:28,125
No, Grandma.
I'll come visit during the week.

439
00:26:29,816 --> 00:26:31,936
The containers are already loaded
into the car.

440
00:26:33,279 --> 00:26:34,949
Just send me the address.

441
00:26:39,267 --> 00:26:41,085
Okay, Grandma. One second.

442
00:26:42,594 --> 00:26:44,168
Your grandmother's coming to our house?

443
00:26:44,828 --> 00:26:47,792
Yes. She made kimchi
and wants to bring some over.

444
00:26:49,421 --> 00:26:52,088
Is it okay if she finds out
you're living at our house?

445
00:26:52,787 --> 00:26:54,210
Grandma will be fine.

446
00:26:54,210 --> 00:26:56,310
If I ask her to keep it secret, she will.

447
00:26:56,808 --> 00:26:58,168
Can I share the address?

448
00:26:58,815 --> 00:26:59,815
Sure.

449
00:27:08,012 --> 00:27:11,312
Isn't this the place we came
with the Chairman last time?

450
00:27:11,632 --> 00:27:15,597
You're right.
Is this really the address Gyeol sent?

451
00:27:16,278 --> 00:27:17,853
Yes. This is it.

452
00:27:18,967 --> 00:27:21,565
Well, look who it is.

453
00:27:22,183 --> 00:27:23,550
Hello.

454
00:27:24,535 --> 00:27:26,413
What brings you here?

455
00:27:27,641 --> 00:27:30,419
Here for some bindaetteok again?

456
00:27:31,109 --> 00:27:33,765
No, not this time.

457
00:27:34,715 --> 00:27:35,824
Where exactly is this?

458
00:27:37,368 --> 00:27:39,595
This is Eun Hyeong's house.

459
00:27:40,402 --> 00:27:44,002
It's the address
of the real estate office?

460
00:27:44,216 --> 00:27:46,712
Yes, 9 Jeongdam-ro 4-gil.

461
00:27:46,712 --> 00:27:48,379
It's inside the real estate office.

462
00:27:48,978 --> 00:27:50,587
What brings you here?

463
00:27:55,124 --> 00:27:58,040
Ma'am, what brings you here?

464
00:27:59,284 --> 00:28:02,211
Then this is...

465
00:28:21,067 --> 00:28:22,167
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
